        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 28 at 2:24AM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 224 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of White Sands Missile Range Main Post, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Sands National Park, White Sands Missile Range Main Post, and
Lake Lucero.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 70 in New Mexico between mile markers 168 and 192.
Highway 54 in New Mexico near mile marker 44.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
